    <p>Home­bound</p>
    <p>SMU (Sin­ga­pore Man­age­ment Univer­sity) Sym­pho­nia presents a dig­i­tal mu­sic pic­ture book of Peter And The Wolf by Sergei Prokofiev, de­con­structed to draw par­al­lels to the pan­demic with child-like whim­si­cal­ity. View­ers will have the op­tion of a read-through or click-through ex­pe­ri­ence as they fol­low Peter in his prepa­ra­tion of a long-awaited con­cert, only to have his dreams ru­ined by the un­ex­pected ar­rival of the Wolf. Part of A-part,</p>
    <p>SMU Arts Fes­ti­val 2020.</p>
    <p>WHEN: Till Oct 30 ADMISSION: Free INFO: smu.sg/arts­fest</p>
    <p>To Gather</p>
    <p>The SMU Chi­nese Orches­tra presents a short four-part doc­u­men­tary se­ries about the mak­ing of a per­for­mance dur­ing Covid-19 and how the mu­sic-mak­ing jour­ney has changed for its mu­si­cians, in­clud­ing a blind gui­tarist, a phys­i­cally dis­abled dizi player and a deaf per­cus­sion­ist. This pro­gramme is a re­cip­i­ent of Cen­tral Sin­ga­pore Com­mu­nity De­vel­op­ment Coun­cil’s Do-Good Grant @ Sin­ga­pore Man­age­ment Univer­sity. Part of</p>
    <p>A-part, SMU Arts Fes­ti­val 2020.</p>
    <p>WHEN: Till Oct 30 ADMISSION: Free INFO: smu.sg/arts­fest</p>


